post_text:
Tonight (4/20/20) GjPS will join other districts across Ohio and the Ohio High School Athletic Association and LIGHT UP THE NIGHT to honor our GLHS Class of 2020. From 8:20 (20:20 military time) until 8:40, the lights at our GLHS football stadium will turn on for 20 minutes to honor our graduating seniors who will complete their final high school year through distance learning.

Please note this is NOT AN INVITATION OR OPPORTUNITY TO ENCOURAGE CONGREGATING OR PEOPLE COMING TO THE STADIUM. Please show your support and unity by staying home and turning on your porch lights!

THE STADIUM WILL REMAIN CLOSED DURING THE LIGHTING! #theGJPSway #gjpsBetterTogether

Happy 3 Days and Counting! On Monday, August 12, GJPS will conduct a test of its messaging system by sending an automated email and phone call to ALL DISTRICT PARENTS between 6 and 8 p.m.

The district uses its messaging system to notify parents of emergencies including school closures, cancellations, and delays.

If you DO NOT receive the email and call, you will need to UPDATE YOUR INFINITE CAMPUS ACCOUNT INFORMATION at www.tinyurl.com/gjpsIC . #gjpsCOUNTDOWN #WelcomeBackGJPS #theGJPSway
